Mexico Auto Output Rose 26.3% in March, Industry Group Says

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-04-13T20:52:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/mexico-auto-output-rose-26-3-in-march-industry-group-says-2-.html
Mexican production of cars and
light trucks rose to 240,080 units in March, a 26.3 percent
increase from the same month a year earlier, the nation’s
 Automobile Industry Association  said.  Exports of vehicles rose 17.8 percent last month to 192,783
units, the group said today in a statement distributed in  Mexico 
City. March’s output and exports mark a monthly record for the
industry, said Eduardo Solis, the head of the association.  Domestic sales increased 14.8 percent to 75,125 vehicles,
according to the statement.  Mexico shipped 120,947 units, or 62.7 percent of cars and
light trucks exported in March, to the U.S. Latin America was
the second-biggest market, buying 16 percent of Mexico’s auto
exports in March, followed by  Europe , with 10.3 percent, the
document said.  Mexican auto industry, including the production of cars and
parts, generated $64.9 billion in exports last year, according
to a report by Citigroup Inc.’s Banamex unit. Mexico received
$41.7 billion from crude and oil derivatives, $21.3 billion from
remittances and $11.9 billion from tourism, Banamex data show.  In the first two months of this year Mexico’s  auto industry 
has exported $11 billion, Banamex said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
